{"tags": [], "refs": [], "refstothis": [], "othertags": [], "uses": [], "user": "wenaus", "logo": "", "usedby": [], "loggedin": true, "mytags": ["intro"], "ent": {"web": null, "mytag": "intro", "description": "<p><a href=\"http://HEPsoftware.org\">HEPsoftware.org</a> / <a href=\"http://HEPcomputing.org\">HEPcomputing.org</a> aspires to become a grass roots information gathering and exchange hub for the HEP software and computing community. Please contribute! Ensure that your experiment, your facility, your favorite software and tools, and your own contributions are properly represented. Sign up in seconds and immediately start submitting and editing entries via simple forms. Power users can also do bulk edits and submissions in simple edit-friendly xml. You can designate new entries as visible only to you and your colleagues while you experiment. The entries will be preserved and archived with their revision history, as all entries are.</p>\n\n<h4>Goals</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Facilitate collaboration by increasing awareness of the activities and resources within our field.</li>\n<li>Engage HEP S&amp;C experts directly in creating and maintaining a useful information resource.</li>\n<li>Offer a grass roots complement to the more structured community activities taking shape, the <a href=\"/e/hsf\">HEP Software Foundation</a> and in the US the <a href=\"/e/fce\">HEP Forum for Computational Excellence</a>.</li>\n<li>Promote, through greater awareness, open source tools and approaches within our community.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Elements thus far</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>This website app</li>\n<li>A <a href=\"/e/reddit\">reddit</a> topic (subreddit) being set up as a discussion forum <a href=\"http://www.reddit.com/r/hepsoftware/\">http://www.reddit.com/r/hepsoftware/</a></li>\n<li>A github project organization to host common repositories <a href=\"https://github.com/hepcode\">https://github.com/hepcode</a>. The first contribution will be the source for this site.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hepsoftware\">@hepsoftware</a> on Twitter where significant developments will be posted. Also as a community we should put the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/hepsoftware\">#hepsoftware</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/hepcomputing\">#hepcomputing</a> hashtags to use!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>This website</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>This is a django app backed by a MySQL database, hosted privately on Amazon EC2.</li>\n<li>The primary data format is xml, with all entries and their revisions preserved in an open, downloadable github repository. </li>\n<li>Entries describe software projects and tools, experiments, facilities, organizations, etc. and can be added and edited by any registered participant, with the revision history preserved in and restorable/revertable from github.</li>\n<li>Entries are formatted using <a href=\"http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax\">markdown</a>, making it easy to implement rich pages with embedded links, images, and structured formatting.</li>\n<li>Tags are used to categorize entries and to represent their interconnections. This is the central purpose of the site -- it isn't intended as a documentation system, it exposes entities and their interconnections with informational links to drill deeper for more information.</li>\n<li>Data entry options currently offered are simple forms in the django app, and user-supplied xml. Form submission is useful for quick and easy casual adding/editing of entries. XML is efficient for bulk editing and submission, or even programmatic submission (but keep in mind the intent of the site is to provide curated information).</li>\n<li>Pages include a link to their xml source as a guide to composing the xml. Also there's <a href=\"/static/entity-template.xml\">an annotated xml template here</a> for use as a starting point for writing your own.</li>\n<li>The site supports a data API so content can be programmatically accessed (as json).</li>\n<li>This initiative was begun mid July 2014 by Torre Wenaus (BNL/ATLAS, wenaus@gmail.com). It is raw and incomplete, and depends on community input and participation to mature and succeed. Please join in and help shape it!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Examples</h4>\n\n<p>Here are some representative pages:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/e/mapneeds\">Muon Accelerator Program (MAP) modeling</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/intensity\">Intensity Frontier</a> and its <a href=\"/s/intensity/\">xml source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/s/intro\">The source for this page</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/lbne\">Long Baseline Neutrino Experiment (LBNE)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/bnl\">Brookhaven National Laboratory (BNL)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/root\">ROOT Data Analysis Framework</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/concurrencyforum\">Concurrency Forum</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/fce\">US HEP Forum for Computational Excellence (FCE)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/hsf\">HEP Software Foundation (HSF)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/panda\">PanDA Production and Distributed Analysis System</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/datamgmt\">Data Access and Management</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/e/us^atlas^tier2\">US ATLAS Tier2s</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>How to contribute</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>This website and other HEPsoftware.org initiatives are fully open to collaboration. The initiatives depend on community participation to mature and thrive.</li>\n<li>To start contributing, take a few moments to sign up via the Account menu, log in and you'll be immediately able to add and edit contributions via simple web forms. You can also make bulk contributions via xml. All contributions are converted to xml and all revisions are preserved in a github repository, offering full access to entry histories and reversion. </li>\n<li>If you use xml submission, you can add content via sources maintained in your own github (or other) repository, including the <a href=\"https://github.com/hepcode\">github hepcode project</a> associated with this site. The workflow will be: edit xml, commit, click or curl (trigger the app to update from your repo and update the DB) and your edits will be live. (This is probably a good job for <a href=\"/e/jenkins\">Jenkins</a>.) The xml is simple and friendly to write. You can see the xml of any entity page in the app (link at the bottom of the page), and there's <a href=\"/static/entity-template.xml\">an annotated xml template here</a>.</li>\n<li>The hepsoftware.org sources will soon appear at <a href=\"https://github.com/hepcode\">github</a>.</li>\n<li>Contact <a href=\"/e/torre_wenaus\">Torre Wenaus</a> to learn more and start contributing!</li>\n</ul>", "created_at": "2014-08-09T14:07:18+00:00", "updated_at": "2014-08-09T14:07:18+00:00", "subtype": "", "location": "", "alltags": " intro ", "date": "2014-08-09T00:00:00+00:00", "description_markup": "[HEPsoftware.org](http://HEPsoftware.org) / [HEPcomputing.org](http://HEPcomputing.org) aspires to become a grass roots information gathering and exchange hub for the HEP software and computing community. Please contribute! Ensure that your experiment, your facility, your favorite software and tools, and your own contributions are properly represented. Sign up in seconds and immediately start submitting and editing entries via simple forms. Power users can also do bulk edits and submissions in simple edit-friendly xml. You can designate new entries as visible only to you and your colleagues while you experiment. The entries will be preserved and archived with their revision history, as all entries are.\n\n#### Goals\n\n* Facilitate collaboration by increasing awareness of the activities and resources within our field.\n* Engage HEP S&amp;C experts directly in creating and maintaining a useful information resource.\n* Offer a grass roots complement to the more structured community activities taking shape, the [HEP Software Foundation](/e/hsf) and in the US the [HEP Forum for Computational Excellence](/e/fce).\n* Promote, through greater awareness, open source tools and approaches within our community.\n\n#### Elements thus far\n* This website app\n* A #reddit topic (subreddit) being set up as a discussion forum [http://www.reddit.com/r/hepsoftware/](http://www.reddit.com/r/hepsoftware/)\n* A github project organization to host common repositories [https://github.com/hepcode](https://github.com/hepcode). The first contribution will be the source for this site.\n* [@hepsoftware](https://twitter.com/hepsoftware) on Twitter where significant developments will be posted. Also as a community we should put the [[[hash]]hepsoftware](https://twitter.com/hashtag/hepsoftware) and [[[hash]]hepcomputing](https://twitter.com/hashtag/hepcomputing) hashtags to use!\n\n#### This website\n\n* This is a django app backed by a MySQL database, hosted privately on Amazon EC2.\n* The primary data format is xml, with all entries and their revisions preserved in an open, downloadable github repository. \n* Entries describe software projects and tools, experiments, facilities, organizations, etc. and can be added and edited by any registered participant, with the revision history preserved in and restorable/revertable from github.\n* Entries are formatted using [markdown](http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax), making it easy to implement rich pages with embedded links, images, and structured formatting.\n* Tags are used to categorize entries and to represent their interconnections. This is the central purpose of the site -- it isn't intended as a documentation system, it exposes entities and their interconnections with informational links to drill deeper for more information.\n* Data entry options currently offered are simple forms in the django app, and user-supplied xml. Form submission is useful for quick and easy casual adding/editing of entries. XML is efficient for bulk editing and submission, or even programmatic submission (but keep in mind the intent of the site is to provide curated information).\n* Pages include a link to their xml source as a guide to composing the xml. Also there's [an annotated xml template here](/static/entity-template.xml) for use as a starting point for writing your own.\n* The site supports a data API so content can be programmatically accessed (as json).\n* This initiative was begun mid July 2014 by Torre Wenaus (BNL/ATLAS, wenaus@gmail.com). It is raw and incomplete, and depends on community input and participation to mature and succeed. Please join in and help shape it!\n\n#### Examples\n\nHere are some representative pages:\n\n* #mapneeds\n* #intensity and its [xml source](/s/intensity/)\n* [The source for this page](/s/intro)\n* #lbne\n* #bnl\n* #root\n* #concurrencyforum\n* #fce\n* #hsf\n* #panda\n* #datamgmt\n* [US ATLAS Tier2s](/e/us^atlas^tier2)\n\n#### How to contribute\n\n* This website and other HEPsoftware.org initiatives are fully open to collaboration. The initiatives depend on community participation to mature and thrive.\n* To start contributing, take a few moments to sign up via the Account menu, log in and you'll be immediately able to add and edit contributions via simple web forms. You can also make bulk contributions via xml. All contributions are converted to xml and all revisions are preserved in a github repository, offering full access to entry histories and reversion. \n* If you use xml submission, you can add content via sources maintained in your own github (or other) repository, including the [github hepcode project](https://github.com/hepcode) associated with this site. The workflow will be: edit xml, commit, click or curl (trigger the app to update from your repo and update the DB) and your edits will be live. (This is probably a good job for #jenkins.) The xml is simple and friendly to write. You can see the xml of any entity page in the app (link at the bottom of the page), and there's [an annotated xml template here](/static/entity-template.xml).\n* The hepsoftware.org sources will soon appear at [github](https://github.com/hepcode).\n* Contact #torre_wenaus to learn more and start contributing!", "type": "content", "id": 290, "allmytags": " intro ", "name": "intro"}, "tagname": "intro", "image": {}}